Here's how the amount is calculated under the current plan:Adults receive a lump sum of $1,200 (or $2,400 for those filing tax returns jointly).
Married couples filing jointly are eligible for a $2,400 check if their household income is below $150,000.
If you set up direct deposit with the IRS for your tax refunds, you should get the money faster than those who will get a check in the mail.
